<item>
            <title>[JDK-8316468] os::write incorrectly handles partial write</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8316468</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8303942&quot; title=&quot;os::write should write completely&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8303942&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8303942&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a bug in os::write() in os.cpp for handling partial write:&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
buf = (void *)((char *)buf + nBytes);&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
should be&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
buf = (void *)((char *)buf + res);&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We observed that in JDK 21, heap dump corruption observed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8303937&quot; title=&quot;Corrupted heap dumps due to missing retries for os::write()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8303937&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8303937&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; happens again when writing to a socket or pipe.</description>
